12/04/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Lawmakers are expected to vote for dissolving parliament on Thursday (April 14th), Speaker Trajko Veljanoski announced on Monday. 
A day later, he will sign a decision to call snap elections on June 5th. 
Veljanoski urged all lawmakers to attend Tuesday's session when a new president of the State Election Commission should be elected. 
The opposition, which continues its parliamentary boycott, has accepted the ruling coalition's proposal to hold early elections in June. 
(MIA, Sitel, Radio Free Europe - 11/04/11)
